jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132297808,imgsize-90602.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Billionaire Melinda Gates could have filled an entire room in her 66,000-square-foot mansion with Hermès Birkin bags. But when her daughter Jennifer wanted a luxury purse, she chose to say no]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132297451.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Melinda French Gates has ingrained the principle of mindful spending into her children's upbringing, emphasizing that wealth should not lead to impulsive indulgence. Through an innovative allowance system, she nurtured habits of saving and early philanthropy. Additionally, the family prioritized hands-on experiences to expand their understanding of the world, ultimately aiming to cultivate a sense of self-worth that transcends their substantial inheritance.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/technology/tech-news/billionaire-melinda-gates-could-have-filled-an-entire-room-in-her-66000-square-foot-mansion-with-herms-birkin-bags-but-when-her-daughter-jennifer-wanted-a-luxury-purse-she-chose-to-say-no/articleshow/132297451.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/technology/tech-news/billionaire-melinda-gates-could-have-filled-an-entire-room-in-her-66000-square-foot-mansion-with-herms-birkin-bags-but-when-her-daughter-jennifer-wanted-a-luxury-purse-she-chose-to-say-no/articleshow/132297451.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T01:19:13+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Tech Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132297797,imgsize-184654.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[What is coincidence? Quote of the day by Carl Jung: 'We often dream about people from whom we receive a letter by the next post']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="le