indiatimes.com/photo/132289879.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The fragile ceasefire between the United States and Iran has collapsed after fresh military strikes. Both nations launched attacks, expanding the conflict across the Gulf region. Iran targeted US air defence systems and facilities in several Middle Eastern countries. The United States struck approximately ninety military sites across Iran. These exchanges marked the biggest breach of the truce since April.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/target-vs-target-what-us-hit-in-iran-and-what-tehran-struck-in-response/articleshow/132289879.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/target-vs-target-what-us-hit-in-iran-and-what-tehran-struck-in-response/articleshow/132289879.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-09T21:04:12+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132291294,imgsize-7614396.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[He manages a $1.4 trillion empire and wears a $140 Swiss watch. Now Stephen Schwarzman has a $400 million superyacht with a glass-bottom pool, helipad and fold-down balconies]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132289821.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Stephen Schwarzman, the chairman of Blackstone, has made headlines by purchasing a lavish superyacht named Destiny. This stunning 101.2-meter craft, which set him back around $400 million, comes from the renowned builder Feadship. Among its luxurious features are a glass-bottom pool and a helipad. Notably, Schwarzman started his remarkable career with a modest $400,000 investment, and he is often seen sporting affordable Swatch watches.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/he-manages-a-1-4-trillion-empire-and-